                    <msContents>
                        <summary>
                            <seg type="para"> This fragment, taken from a 17th-century manuscript,
                                contains an incomplete copy of the <title>Refutation of the union of
                                    the Churches</title> by patriarchs <name>
                           <persName type="standard">Philotheus of Alexandria</persName>
                        </name>,
                                        <name>
                           <persName type="standard">Dorotheus of
                                        Antioch</persName>
                        </name>, and <name>
                           <persName type="standard">Joachim of Jerusalem</persName>
                        </name>. The
                                text comes from the Council of Jerusalem of 1443, in which the
                                Eastern Patriarchs met to condemn the union of the Catholic and
                                Orthodox churches, negotiated at the Council of Ferrara-Florence
                                (1438-1439). The Patriarchs also condemned Metrophanes, Patriarch of
                                Constantinople, who supported the union of the Churches. It was
                                decreed that no clerk ordained by the Oriental bishops in communion
                                with Rome should be admitted to exercise his office in their
                                communion, until he had in the presence of the orthodox bishops
                                proved his adhesion to the Greek Church.</seg>
                            <seg type="para"> The Refutation is followed by some quotations from
                                church fathers on the procession of the Holy Spirit in opposition to
                                the Western doctrine of <hi rend="italic">Filioque</hi>. In
                                particular, the quotations attributed to Gregory of Nyssa and Cyril
                                of Alexandria seem to have been taken from Gregory of Palamas, <hi rend="italic">De processione Spiritus Sancti</hi>, whose order
                                they follow.</seg>
                            <seg type="para">The fragment was acquired by Constantin von Tischendorf
                                and bought from his heirs by Cambridge University Library in
                                1876.</seg>
                            <seg type="para">Dr Matteo Di Franco</seg>
                        </summary>

                        <textLang mainLang="grc">Greek</textLang>

                        <msItem n="1">
                            <locus from="1r" to="2v">ff. 1r-2v</locus>
                            <author>Philotheus of Alexandria</author>
                            <author>Dorotheus of Antioch</author>
                            <author>Joachim of Jerusalem</author>
                            <title xml:lang="eng">Refutation of the Council of
                                Ferrara-Florence</title>
                            <title type="alt" xml:lang="la">Definitio patriarcharum sanctorum
                                Syriae</title>
                            <rubric>
                        <locus from="1r" to="1r">f. 1r</locus> Ὅρος τῶν ἁγιωτάτων
                                    π<ex>ατ</ex>ριαρχῶν· Φιλοθέου Ἀλεξανδρείας· Δωροθέου Ἀντιοχείας·
                                Ἰωακεὶμ Ἱεροσολύμων ἐπ' ἀνατροπῇ τῆς ἐν Φλωρεντίᾳ συνόδου γεγονὼς·
                                καὶ καθαιρέσεως τοῦ Κυζίκου Μητροφάνους γενομένου
                                π<ex>ατ</ex>ριάρχου Κωνσταντινοπόλεως</rubric>
                            <incipit>
                        <locus from="1r" to="1r">f. 1r</locus> Ἐπειδὴ ἦκε· καὶ ὁ
                                πανιερώτατος μ<ex>ητ</ex>ροπολίτης ἐνταῦθα τῆς ἁγιωτάτης
                                    μ<ex>ητ</ex>ροπόλεως Καισαρείας</incipit>
                            <explicit defective="true">
                        <locus from="2v" to="2v">f. 2v</locus>
                                κενοδοξίας μόνης καὶ αἱρέσεως τρόπῳ πρὸς ἐπισκοπάς τε καὶ
                                    μ<ex>ητ</ex>ροπόλεις ὡς δῆθεν τάχα σωτῆρας ψυχῶν</explicit>
                            <note>ed. <bibl>G. Hofmann, <hi rend="italic">Concilium Florentinum,
                                        Documenta et Scriptores</hi>, Ser. A, <hi rend="italic">Orientalium Documenta Minora</hi>, vol. III fasc. III, Roma
                                    1953, p. 68-72</bibl>, at pp. 69-71 line 24; cf. PG 147,
                                532-534</note>
                        </msItem>

                        <msItem n="2">
                            <locus from="3r" to="3v">ff. 3r-3v</locus>
                            <title xml:lang="eng">Patristic citations on the Procession
                                of the Holy Spirit</title>
                            <rubric>
                        <locus from="3r" to="3r">f. 3r</locus> Δαμασκηνοῦ, ἐν τῷ η<hi rend="superscript">ω</hi> τῶν θελογικῶν</rubric>
                            <incipit>
                        <locus from="1r" to="1r">f. 1r</locus> ἐν ταύταις μόναις ταῖς
                                ὑποστατικαῖς ἰδιότησι τῇ ἀγεννησίᾳ</incipit>
                            <explicit defective="true">
                        <locus from="2v" to="2v">f. 2v</locus> ὡς
                                δῆθεν τάχα σωτῆρας ψυχῶν</explicit>
                            <note>Extracts from John of Damascus, <hi rend="italic">Expositio
                                    fidei</hi> (TLG 2934.004); Athanasius of Alexandria (attributed
                                to), <hi rend="italic">Quaestiones aliae</hi> (TLG 2035.081); Basil
                                of Caesarea, cf. <hi rend="italic">Adversus Eunomium</hi> (TLG
                                2040.019); Gregory of Nyssa (attributed to), <hi rend="italic">De
                                    cognitione Dei</hi> (CPG 3223); Cyril of Alexandria (attributed
                                to), <hi rend="italic">De sancta trinitate</hi> (CPG 5432) and <hi rend="italic">Ὁμολογία πίστεως</hi>: cf. Gregory Palamas, <hi rend="italic">De processione Spiritus Sancti</hi>, I 19, TLG
                                3254.004).</note>
                        </msItem>
